1. Document Structure & Metadata
<html> – Root element of an HTML document.
<head> – Contains metadata, links to stylesheets, and other information for the document.
<meta> – Provides metadata about the HTML document (charset, viewport, etc.).
<title> – Sets the title of the web page (shown on the browser tab).
<link> – Links external resources (usually stylesheets).
<style> – Embeds internal CSS styles.
<script> – Embeds or references a JavaScript code.

2. Content Structure
<body> – Contains the visible content of the HTML document.
<header> – Represents the introductory content or set of navigational links.
<nav> – Defines navigation links.
<section> – Defines a section in a document.
<article> – Represents an independent piece of content.
<aside> – Defines content related to the main content, such as sidebars.
<footer> – Defines the footer for a section or page.
<div> – Defines a block-level division or section (common for layout).
<span> – Defines an inline section.

3. Text Formatting & Headings
<h1> to <h6> – Defines headings from highest importance (<h1>) to lowest (<h6>).
<p> – Defines a paragraph.
<strong> – Displays text in bold, indicating strong importance.
<em> – Displays text in italics, indicating emphasis.
<b> – Boldens text (for stylistic purposes).
<i> – Italicizes text (for stylistic purposes).
<br> – Inserts a line break.
<hr> – Inserts a horizontal line (thematic break).

4. Lists
<ul> – Creates an unordered list (bulleted).
<ol> – Creates an ordered list (numbered).
<li> – Defines a list item within <ul> or <ol>.
5. Links & Media
<a> – Defines a hyperlink.
<img> – Embeds an image.
<audio> – Embeds audio content.
<video> – Embeds video content.
<source> – Defines media resources for media elements (<audio> and <video>).
<figure> – Specifies self-contained content like images, diagrams, or code blocks.
<figcaption> – Provides a caption for the <figure> element.
<iframe> – Embeds another HTML page within the current page.
<canvas> – Used for drawing graphics via JavaScript.

6. Tables
<table> – Defines a table.
<thead> – Groups the header content in a table.
<tbody> – Groups the body content in a table.
<tfoot> – Groups the footer content in a table.
<tr> – Defines a row in a table.
<th> – Defines a header cell in a table.
<td> – Defines a standard cell in a table.

7. Forms & Inputs
<form> – Creates a form for user input.
<input> – Defines an input control (text fields, checkboxes, etc.).
<button> – Creates a clickable button.
<label> – Associates a label with a form element.
<textarea> – Creates a multi-line text input area.
<select> – Creates a dropdown list.
<option> – Defines an option within a dropdown list.
